<head>DROWN</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>SUFFOCATE IN WATER</item>
<item>INHALE WATER</item>
<item>GO TO A WATERY GRAVE</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">溺死</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">溺</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>DIE BECAUSE of SINKING into WATER.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1.The current general word for seeking death by drowning or dying through drowning is nì 溺.</p>
<p>2. A very common term for drowning oneself is zì tóu 自投.</p>
<p>3. Chén 沉／沈 refers to submerging either oneself or things, sometimes in order to drown them. See SINK</p>
        </div>
